# SpriteAnimationSystem

## Purpose
Engine sprite-sheet frame stepper. Sole writer of SpriteAnimationComponent and the modifying writer of
SpriteComponent's sub-texture. For every entity carrying both a SpriteAnimationComponent and a
SpriteComponent it first applies any SetSpriteAnimationRequestOneFrameComponent present on that entity
(switching the active animation row when requested and toggling playback). When playing, it advances the
animation timer by the frame delta and steps the active row's current column forward, wrapping at the
configured frame count; when paused it resets to the idle frame. It then writes the active sheet cell's
normalised UV rectangle into the SpriteComponent. No-ops when no animated sprites exist. Registered by
the engine in Application::Init.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SetSpriteAnimationRequestOneFrameComponent | read | Optional per-entity row switch + playback toggle (emitted by the app) |
| SpriteAnimationComponent | write | Playback state read for parameters and advanced in place |
| SpriteComponent | write | Sub-texture UV rectangle rewritten each frame |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SpriteAnimationComponent | write | m_Elapsed + m_Column advanced (or reset to the idle frame when paused), m_Row/m_Playing applied from the request |
| SpriteComponent | write | m_TexCoordsRect set to the active cell's UV rectangle from the SpriteSheet |
